BT 1 0 0 1 0 58 Tm /F1 10 Tf 17 TL .87875 Tw (Colors have temperature: reds, oranges, and yellows are warm; blues, greens, and violets are cool. This is) Tj T* 0 Tw .132778 Tw (not just emotional \227 it has real optical effects. Warm colors appear to advance \(come forward in space\); cool) Tj T* 0 Tw -0.079474 Tw (colors appear to recede. In natural light, lit areas are often warm and shadow areas cool \(or vice versa\). Using) Tj T* 0 Tw (temperature contrast in your shading creates luminous, convincing light.) Tj T* ET
